Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.96,0:00:08.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}眼见并不为实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Seeing is not believing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.57,0:00:10.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的感官会误导我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our senses can deceive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.97,0:00:13.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些星星并不是我们看到的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the stars are not what they appear to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.81,0:00:16.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过科学展示出的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmos, as revealed by science,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.31,0:00:19.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比我们所能想象的更离奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is stranger than we ever could have imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.64,0:00:24.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光 时间 空间 万有引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light and time and space and gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:26.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}共同创造出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}conspire to create realities
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.15,0:00:29.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们从未体验过的现实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which lie beyond human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.69,0:00:31.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们一探究竟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's where we're headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.76,0:00:34.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跟我来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.66,0:00:39.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1802年 像这样的一个夜晚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in 1802, on a night like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.83,0:00:42.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家威廉・赫歇尔和他的儿子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the astronomer William Herschel strolled the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:45.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在英国海边散步\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the English coast, with his son John.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.60,0:00:48.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫歇尔是有史以来第一位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Herschel was the first person ever
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.60,0:00:48.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}恒星天文学之父
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.51,0:00:51.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看穿宇宙深层奥秘的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see into the deeper waters of the cosmic ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.61,0:00:55.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他看穿了光线和时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There he glimpsed the magic trick
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.85,0:00:57.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一起变出的戏法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that light does with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.72,0:00:59.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}父亲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.62,0:01:01.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你相信有鬼魂吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}do you believe in ghosts?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.72,0:01:03.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎么了  我相信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why, yes, my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.56,0:01:06.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You, you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.12,0:01:07.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我真没想到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I would not have thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.63,0:01:11.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是人死后的鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oh, no, not in the human kind of ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.36,0:01:13.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}绝不是那种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No... not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.13,0:01:15.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抬头看 儿子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But look up, my boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.63,0:01:18.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天空中满是鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and see a sky full of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.47,0:01:20.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星星  父亲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.57,0:01:22.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我没听懂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I do not follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.21,0:01:27.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个星星都像我们的太阳那么亮 那么大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every star is a sun as big, as bright as our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:31.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想看要把太阳移到多远以外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just imagine how far away from us you'd have to move the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.42,0:01:35.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才能让它看上去像星星那样小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make it appear as small and faint as a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.09,0:01:38.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星星发出的光 速度很快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light from the stars travels very fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.89,0:01:40.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最快的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}faster than anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:43.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但并不是无限的快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not infinitely fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.06,0:01:46.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星光到达我们这里需要时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It takes time for their light to reach us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.90,0:01:50.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最近的可能需要几年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the nearest ones, it takes years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.07,0:01:52.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它那些  几百年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For others, centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.67,0:01:55.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一些特别远的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some stars are so far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.17,0:01:59.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}需要亿万年才能到达地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it takes eons for their light to get to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:03.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}等那些星星发出的光到达这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the time the light from some stars gets here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.92,0:02:06.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星星已经死了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they are already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.42,0:02:10.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对这些星星来说  我们看到的只是他们的鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For those stars, we see only their ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.02,0:02:13.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们看到他们的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see their light,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:16.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他们的星球已经死了很久很久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but their bodies perished long, long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:22.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约翰  我比我们的古人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}John, I have seen further back in time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:24.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能看到更古老的过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than any man before me--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.54,0:02:27.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几百万年前的过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}millions of years into the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.88,0:02:32.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威廉・赫歇尔是第一个认识到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}William Herschel was the first person to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:35.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}望远镜就是一个时间机器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that a telescope is a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:38.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们看向太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We cannot look out into space
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.05,0:02:40.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是看向过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without seeing back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.32,0:02:46.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一秒钟  光穿越30万公里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In one second, light travels 300,000 kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.63,0:02:49.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者18万6千英里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or 186,000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:51.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎就是地球到月亮的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's nearly the distance from the Earth to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:55.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以月亮离我们1光秒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, the Moon is about one light-second away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:57.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}下次你看向月亮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The next time you look at the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:03:00.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你就会看到1秒钟以前的过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll be seeing one second into the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.63,0:04:35.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第四集
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:43.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.54,0:04:45.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不真的在那个位置\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's not really there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:47.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳实际上升出地平线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't actually be above the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:49.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是两分钟以后的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for another two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.75,0:04:52.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日出只是个幻象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sunrise is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.12,0:04:54.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大气层使射入的阳光发生了折射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth's atmosphere bends the incoming rays of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:57.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像镜片和一杯水那样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like a lens or a glass of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:01.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们看到的只是地平线之上的投影\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we see the image of the Sun projected above the horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:03.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳本身还没到达那个位置\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before the physical Sun is actually there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:07.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我身后的太阳只是海市蜃楼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That Sun behind me is a mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:09.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像那闪烁的图像\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No more real than the shimmering image
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:10.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}漂浮在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that hovers in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:13.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}炎热天气下的沙漠远方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over a desert road on a hot day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.94,0:05:16.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日光需要8分钟才能达到地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sunlight takes about eight minutes to reach Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.94,0:05:20.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳离我们8光分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so the Sun is eight light-minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:22.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对于太阳来说  我们只能看到它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From Earth, we can only ever see the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:24.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}8分钟之前的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it was eight minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:28.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一件事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And another thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.29,0:05:30.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳并不是真的 升起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun doesn't really "rise" at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:32.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球带着我们一起旋转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth turns and we turn with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:37.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看上去也许不像  但是这个时候\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may not look like it, but right at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.23,0:05:39.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我比飞机走的还快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm moving faster than a jet plane
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.63,0:05:42.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你也是  其它所有人都一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so are you and everyone on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.13,0:05:43.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我看过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While I'm at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.34,0:05:44.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地平线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:46.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不真的存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's not really there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.14,0:05:48.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根本没有边缘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.47,0:05:50.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地平线也只是一种幻象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The horizon is just another illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:08.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球离最外围的行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The distance between Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:10.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海王星的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the outermost planet Neptune
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:13.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随着环日轨道而不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}varies as the planets orbit the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:16.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}平均来说  光要4个小时才能传来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On average, the light makes that trip in four hours.
