Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:06.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但就算离我们3千万光年之外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even 30 million light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:10.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从宇宙中看 也不过就在我们的后院\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is still in our own cosmic backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:16.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个星系属于后发座星系团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That galaxy is part of the Coma Cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:19.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}3亿2千万光年之遥\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}320 million light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:21.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当这里的光出发时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was going on back home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.47,0:11:24.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时的地球又是怎样的呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the light you are seeing began its trip to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.48,0:11:29.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有我们熟悉的大陆  海洋  河流\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No familiar continents, oceans or rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.75,0:11:33.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的远古祖先刚刚从水中登上陆地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our distant ancestors were just leaving the water for the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:35.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很古老的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's pretty old light,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:38.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但远不是 我们能看到的 最古老的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not nearly the oldest light we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:44.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最古老的光已经很微弱了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The oldest light is very faint,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:46.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}暗夜中虚弱的鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a pale ghost in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.43,0:11:49.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到圆圈中的红点吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that red blob inside the circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.50,0:11:52.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是我们能见的最古老星系之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's one of the oldest galaxies we've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:58.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你看到的是134亿岁高龄的星光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're looking at 13.4-billion year-old starlight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.04,0:12:01.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过哈勃太空望远镜捕捉到的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as captured by the Hubble space telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:12.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它来自第一代的星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's coming from the very first generation of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.62,0:12:15.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时的地球什么情况\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was happening on Earth back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.19,0:12:17.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}完全没情况\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Absolutely nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:21.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时 没有地球 没有太阳 没有银河系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was no Earth, no Sun, no Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:24.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们都是几十亿年后才诞生的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They would not come to be for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:30.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我们看向宇宙的更深处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we try to look even farther into the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:33.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好像已经到了宇宙的尽头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we come to what appears to be the end of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.38,0:12:37.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但事实上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.25,0:12:39.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是时间的开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:48.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球向下拉着我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth pulls on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:51.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们不断地反抗引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our lives are a relentless struggle with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.43,0:13:08.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个小女孩用尽全力要爬出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That little girl is trying her best to climb out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.76,0:13:11.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}引力的包围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a gravitational well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.03,0:13:14.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从第一次尝试站立到最后的倒下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From our first efforts to stand to our final surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:18.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们一直在努力克服地心引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we are struggling to overcome the Earth's pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.44,0:13:23.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在重力场中诞生  生活  过世\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are born, live and die in a force field--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:27.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重力场几乎和宇宙本身一样的古老\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that is almost as old as the universe itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:30.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有多古老\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And how old is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:34.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了想象宇宙的138亿年岁月\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To visualize the 13.8 billion year age of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:35.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们把所有的宇宙时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've compressed all of cosmic time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:38.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}压缩在一份单张的年历中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a single year-at-a-glance calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.13,0:13:42.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在是12月31号的午夜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Midnight on December 31 is this very moment right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:46.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而1月1号就是时间的开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And January 1 is the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.00,0:13:49.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那耀眼的烟雾吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that glowing fog out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.40,0:13:52.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是大爆炸遗留下的辐射物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's radiation left over from the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:54.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在138亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the explosion that made the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:57.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大爆炸创造了宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}13.8 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.91,0:14:03.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在 我们站在已知空间和时间的边缘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right now, we're at the very edge of known space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.59,0:14:07.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么 大爆炸之前是什么样子呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what happened before the Big Bang?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没人知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:12.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有丝毫关于那之前的证据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No evidence survives from before that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:14.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们有一些很疯狂的猜想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've got some pretty crazy ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:15.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是关于宇宙的来源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about where the universe came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们以后会提到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which we'll get to, in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:21.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在宇宙的什么位置\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where are we in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:24.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在正中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the very center.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:28.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在已知宇宙中 每个人都觉得自己很特殊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the observed universe, everyone gets to feel special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:31.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论你身处哪个星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No matter which galaxy you happen to live in,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.55,0:14:34.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当你看向宇宙时  你会发现自己\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you look out to the universe, you'll find yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.68,0:14:37.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}身处宇宙地平线的中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the center of the cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:39.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这不过是个错觉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this is just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:41.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}实际上  没有中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In reality, there is no center,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:46.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙地平线和海上的地平线 一样不真实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the cosmic horizon is no more real than the horizon at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:51.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是因为 在有起始时间的宇宙中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's what you get when you have a finite speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:54.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光速是有限的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a universe that had a beginning in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:15:00.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大爆炸后的几亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few hundred million years after the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.38,0:15:03.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大量的氢气和氦气云团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}vast clouds of hydrogen and helium condensed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:06.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}凝结成最初的恒星和星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the first stars and galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.82,0:15:08.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有了这些新的光源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With these new sources of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:11.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙漫长的黑暗时代从此终结\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the long dark ages of the universe ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.42,0:15:13.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随着宇宙的不断膨胀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As space continued to expand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:17.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙进化的规模变得更加宏大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cosmic evolution unfolded on grander scales.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:20.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最初的星星死亡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the first generation of stars died,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:23.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们将较重的元素散布在宇宙中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they seeded space with heavier elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:26.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使得行星的形成 成为可能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making possible the formation of planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.07,0:15:29.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 生命的形成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ultimately, life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.24,0:15:36.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大爆炸形成了物质和能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Matter and energy were formed in the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:38.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:40.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}创造了空间和时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space and time were created, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:43.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有束缚所有物质的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all the forces that bind matter together,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括 重力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:46.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿发现了一个数学定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton discovered a mathematical law
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.02,0:15:49.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以形容重力的运作机制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that describes how gravity works.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:52.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他可以用它解释行星间的运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With that law, he could explain the motions of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:54.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}100多年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More than 100 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:58.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威廉・赫歇尔 意识到 那还不是全部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}William Herschel realized gravity could do much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:08.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约翰 你能保守秘密吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}John, can you keep a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.28,0:16:10.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以 父亲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:14.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我有了一个发现  还没告诉过任何人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've made a discovery and have yet to tell another soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:19.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的地心引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity that holds us to the Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:21.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同样是牛顿发现的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same gravity that Newton showed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:23.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将行星保持在轨道上的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}keeps the planets in their orbits--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:24.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.63,0:16:28.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也同样适用于 相隔遥远的恒星们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it also rules the distant stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:32.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爹  你咋知道的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Father... but how can you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:35.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能找到狮子座吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you find the constellation of the Lion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.14,0:16:39.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:40.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}干得好\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.84,0:16:43.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能找到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you now find the star
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.48,0:16:46.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}连接头部和身体的那颗星吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that joins the Lion's head to his body?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.82,0:16:48.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:51.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那其实是两颗星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That star is really two stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:55.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}靠的很近 看上去就像一颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so close together that they appear to be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.52,0:16:58.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我用望远镜观察了很久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've been watching them through my telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:00.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你出生很久前就开始了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since long before you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:05.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们非常缓慢的 围绕相互移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They dance around each other very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.43,0:17:09.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远比行星绕恒星运动的慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More slowly than any planet moves around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:14.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们今晚看到的许多星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of the stars we see tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:16.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能大部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps most of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:18.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照看不见的规律移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dance with invisible partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:24.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}万有引力这个大帝国统治着所有的星球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity's empire governs all the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:35.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1个世纪前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A century earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.06,0:17:36.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}艾萨克・牛顿备受困扰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton had been haunted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:40.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他也找不到引力的作用机制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the same absence of a mechanism for gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.04,0:17:42.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相距甚远的物体 如何相互影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could distant bodies affect each other
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:46.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不用接触就相互影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across empty space without actually touching?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:50.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个他称之为 超距作用 的问题困扰着他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This "action at a distance," as he called it, baffled him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}19世纪 迈克尔・法拉第（电学之父）发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 19th century, Michael Faraday discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}电学之父
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:58.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们被不可见的力场包围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we were surrounded by invisible fields of force
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.99,0:18:01.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这解释了引力的运作机制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that explained how gravity works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.72,0:18:04.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}苹果和地球 并没有发生接触\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The apple and the Earth don't touch each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:06.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是他们之间的力场产生了接触\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the fields between them do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:10.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他想象引力产生的线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He imagined those lines of gravitational force
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.57,0:18:13.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从每一个物体 向太空中辐射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}radiating out into space from every massive body--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.60,0:18:18.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球 月亮 太阳  所有的一切\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth, the Moon, the Sun, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是那个困扰牛顿的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here was the answer to that question
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:24.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}的答案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that had stumped Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:29.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1985年 詹姆斯・克拉克・麦克斯韦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1865, James Clerk Maxwell translated Faraday's idea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:31.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把法拉第关于电磁场的理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about fields of electricity and magnetism
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:34.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}转化成了数学公式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into mathematical laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:38.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发现这些磁场 电场都以波的形式在空间中移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He discovered that these fields move through space in waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:41.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当他计算它们的移动速度时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When he calculated how fast they move,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:44.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}结果是 光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it turned out to be the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:48.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们才发现了  宇宙这个大挂毯上的线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We were beginning to discover the threads of the cosmic tapestry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:51.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们还无法 看出丰富的图案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we were not yet able to discern the rich pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:55.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间 光 空间 重力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that time, light, space and gravity weave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:56.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿尔伯特・爱因斯坦 在柏林\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As Albert Einstein worked in Berlin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.81,0:18:58.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}研究他的引力理论时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on his theory of gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:02.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}墙上挂了这3位前辈的头像\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he kept the portraits of these three men before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.38,0:19:05.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他知道他的成就  建立在他们的基础上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He knew he was standing on their shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.75,0:19:08.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}多年前  少年时  他有过一个顿悟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Years before, as a teenager, he had an insight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:12.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同前辈们的理论那般惊天动地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was as Earth-shaking as any idea of theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:14.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那年夏天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it happened one summer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.13,0:19:16.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在意大利遐想时的顿悟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while he was daydreaming in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:27.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1895年的夏天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the summer of 1895,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.54,0:19:30.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他父亲在德国的生意失败\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein's father's business in Germany had failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.37,0:19:32.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全家搬到了意大利北部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the family had moved here to northern Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.88,0:19:35.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小爱因斯坦喜欢在这些路上散步\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Young Einstein loved wandering these roads
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:38.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让他的思维随意发散\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and giving his mind free rein to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.55,0:19:42.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里有着某些永恒的东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's something timeless about this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:45.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和爱因斯坦最初的遐想时相比\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing here has really changed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.56,0:19:48.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}基本没什么变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since the time of Einstein's early daydreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:56.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一天 他想到了光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One day, he began to think about light
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.23,0:19:58.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有光速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how fast it travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:20:00.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日常生活中 我们总是测量物体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In everyday life, we always measure the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.97,0:20:03.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相对于其它物体的移动速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a moving object with respect to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:06.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}假设其它物体没有移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something that's presumably not moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.91,0:20:09.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中的其它物体没有运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something in the cosmos that's not in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.01,0:20:13.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比方说  我的速度大约每小时10公里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, I'm moving about ten kilometers per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:16.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相对于地面而言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}relative to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.29,0:20:19.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但我之前提过  大地也在运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as I mentioned earlier, the ground is moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.36,0:20:23.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的转速超过每小时1600公里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth is turning at more than 1,600 kilometers per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.76,0:20:25.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在环日轨道上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while it orbits the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:28.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}速度超过每小时10万公里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at more than 100,000 kilometers per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:30.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且太阳系在银河系中运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the Sun is moving through the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约为每小时90万公里
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每小时50万英里的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a half a million miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:36.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系在宇宙中运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the Milky Way is moving through the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}实际约为216万公里
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}速度将近每小时150万英里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at nearly one and a half million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:42.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中没有不动的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is no fixed place in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:44.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一切都在运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of nature is in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.15,0:20:48.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对小爱因斯坦来说  也是很难想象出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was hard even for the young Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:50.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个绝对的标准\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to imagine some absolute standard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:54.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用来衡量所有这些相对的运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to measure all those relative motions against.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.84,0:21:09.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是这本书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the very book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:11.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}启发了少年爱因斯坦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that inspired Einstein as a young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:16.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给了他一本书  改变了这个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Give a kid a book and you change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.68,0:21:18.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}某种程度上  改变了这个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a way, even the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.02,0:21:22.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看这里  第一页\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Look at this-- the very first page,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:24.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它描述了令人惊讶的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it describes the astonishing speed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.49,0:21:26.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电流通过电线的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of electricity through wires
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.26,0:21:28.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光穿过宇宙的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and light through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.86,0:21:32.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦记得他小时候从这本书里学到的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein remembered what he'd learned as a child from this book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:35.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许 最初 就在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps, for the first time, right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.93,0:21:37.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象着这个世界将会如何\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wondered what the world would look like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:40.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果可以用光速运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you could travel at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.34,0:21:46.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦越想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The more Einstein thought about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.84,0:21:48.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}越觉得困惑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more troubled he became.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.75,0:21:52.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你想象以光速运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you imagine traveling at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:55.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}各个方面都充满了矛盾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}paradoxes seem to pop up everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.95,0:21:58.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦惊讶的发现 如此众多的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein was shocked to realize that so much
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.76,0:22:00.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使是被最伟大的权威人士\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what had been uncritically accepted as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.79,0:22:03.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无条件接受的真理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by even the greatest authorities on the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:04.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}竟是大错特错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was just plain wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.60,0:22:08.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以高速运动时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When traveling at high speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.97,0:22:11.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}必须遵守一些特定的规则\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are certain rules which must be obeyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.94,0:22:14.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦称之为 相对性原理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein called these rules "The Principles of Relativity."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.71,0:22:17.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象刚才那位呼啸而过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine that young woman who just blew past us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.41,0:22:18.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}骑摩托的年轻女士\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the motorbike,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.88,0:22:20.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象她骑车穿行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}imagine she was riding her bike
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.38,0:22:23.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在宇宙中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.41,0:22:26.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从移动的物体上发出的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light from a moving object travels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.05,0:22:28.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论物体是静止还是移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the same speed, no matter whether the object
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.05,0:22:30.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}速度都是一样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is at rest or in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.96,0:22:33.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她的速度并不会增加光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Her speed is not added to the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.89,0:22:35.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从她的摩托车发出的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light from her motorbike
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.73,0:22:38.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}依然是光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}still travels at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.93,0:22:41.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大自然的谕旨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nature commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.73,0:22:45.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}汝不可超越光速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Thou shalt not add my speed to the speed of light."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.57,0:22:48.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同样 没有物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Also, no material object
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.14,0:22:50.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}传播速度可以达到或者超过光速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can travel at or faster than the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:52.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物理上 没有什么可以阻止你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's nothing in physics that prevents you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.84,0:22:55.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随心所欲地接近光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from traveling as close to the speed of light as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.45,0:22:59.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}99.9%的光速 没问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}99.9% of the speed of light is just fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:01.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是无论你怎么努力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but no matter how hard you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.59,0:23:04.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都无法得到 最后的那个百分点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you never gain that last decimal point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.09,0:23:06.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以现实的逻辑一致性来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For reality to be logically consistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:09.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}必然存在一个宇宙速度极限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there must be a cosmic speed limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:19.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鞭子发出的声音是因为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crack of that whip is due to its tip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.27,0:23:21.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鞭头的移动速度超过了声速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving faster than the speed of sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.27,0:23:23.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生了冲击波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It makes a shockwave,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.11,0:23:25.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}例如这个在意大利乡村的 一个小小的音爆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mini sonic boom, in the Italian countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.31,0:23:30.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}打雷也是一样的道理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A thunderclap works the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.51,0:23:33.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有超音速飞机掠过时的声音\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so does the sound of a passing supersonic jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.65,0:23:35.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那为什么光速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why is the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.99,0:23:38.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比音速更难超越\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any more a barrier than the speed of sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:40.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}答案是 不仅仅光速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The answer is not just that light travels
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.89,0:23:43.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比音速快100万倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a million times faster than sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:45.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也因为 这不仅是一个工程学问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's not merely an engineering problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.56,0:23:47.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像建造首架超音速飞机那种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like building the first supersonic jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.13,0:23:49.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光障\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, the light barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.53,0:23:51.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是自然的基本定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a fundamental law of nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.47,0:23:53.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像万有引力一样基本\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as basic as gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.34,0:23:56.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦为这个世界设定了绝对的准则\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein found his absolute framework for the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.64,0:23:58.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这给了宇宙运动中的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this sturdy pillar among all the relative motions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.71,0:24:01.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有相对运动强有力的支持\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}within the motions of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:03.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光速就是那么快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light travels just as fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.21,0:24:07.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无论光源移动的快慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter how fast or slow its source is moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:11.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相对其他任何东西 光速是恒定的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Speed of light is constant, relative to everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.39,0:24:13.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有什么可以追上光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing can ever catch up with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.86,0:24:17.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自然定律的伟大就是在于\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thing about the laws of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.00,0:24:19.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们无懈可击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that they're unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.90,0:24:22.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物理学家的工作就是发现这些定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The job of physicists is to discover these commandments,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.90,0:24:25.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}定律不随文化的不同而改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ones that do not vary from culture to culture
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.87,0:24:27.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不随时间而改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or time to time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.54,0:24:29.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放之宇宙而皆准\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hold true throughout the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.67,0:24:32.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是为何  如同爱因斯坦指出的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why, as Einstein showed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.78,0:24:36.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接近光速时就出问题了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}funny things happen close to the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.62,0:24:42.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以接近光速的速度旅行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Traveling close to the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:45.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像是长生不老药\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is kind of an elixir of life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.12,0:24:48.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的生物钟慢下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because your biological clock slows down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.13,0:24:50.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相对于其它人来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}relative to those you leave behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.29,0:24:52.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种现象或许可以为我们人类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This phenomenon may provide us humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.96,0:24:55.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只能活1个世纪左右的人类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who only live for a century or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.03,0:24:57.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}提供一个可行的恒星间旅行的方案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a practical means to travel to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.47,0:24:59.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时空魔法大戏\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the magic show of spacetime
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.64,0:25:02.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}精彩纷呈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really gets crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.59,0:25:15.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}19世纪的天文学家 威廉・赫歇尔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 19th-century astronomer William Herschel
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.52,0:25:17.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}喜欢和他的儿子约翰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}loved to share the wonders of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.83,0:25:19.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分享宇宙中的奇迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with his son John.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.67,0:25:34.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我有个朋友 一个很聪明的家伙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I once had a friend, very clever fellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.11,0:25:36.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家 也是里兹的牧师\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an astronomer and a parson at Leeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.28,0:25:38.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}叫 约翰・米切尔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the name of John Michell.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:41.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你还是婴儿时 他就过世了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Poor man died when you were a babe,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.62,0:25:43.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}愿他安息\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}God rest his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.55,0:25:45.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他坚信有些星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He held that some stars
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.62,0:25:47.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}虽然看不到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.62,0:25:50.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}却确实存在 但是我们永远无法看到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They really exist, but we shall never see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.96,0:25:54.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}米切尔叫他们 「暗星」\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Dark stars," Michell called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.06,0:25:58.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恕我直言 父亲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With all due respect, Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.20,0:26:00.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你的朋友肯定弄错了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}surely your friend was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.80,0:26:02.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果没人能看到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If no one can see them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.47,0:26:05.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们怎么能知道它们确实存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then how can we possibly know they exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.81,0:26:10.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你看到留下脚印的人了吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Did you see the man who left those footprints, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.31,0:26:12.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没 怎么了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why, no, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.81,0:26:13.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我没看到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.81,0:26:16.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但你知道他们确实存在 不是吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But do you know that he exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.67,0:26:36.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约翰 米切尔是最伟大的科学家之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}John Michell is one of the greatest scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.57,0:26:38.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你可能从没听说过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you've probably never heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.94,0:26:41.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他生活工作于18世纪的英格兰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He lived and worked in England in the 18th century.
