Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.47,0:37:48.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}萎缩恒星内部的引力 相提并论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with what goes on inside a collapsed star.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.93,0:37:51.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据我们所知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As far as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.04,0:37:54.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当超大恒星萎缩成黑洞时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when a giant star collapses to make a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.77,0:37:56.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中心产生极大的密度和压力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the extreme density and pressure at the center
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.54,0:38:01.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同诞生宇宙的大爆炸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mimic the Big Bang, which gave rise to our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.31,0:38:03.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}于是黑洞内诞生了一个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a universe inside a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.05,0:38:05.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这宇宙可能会产生它自己的黑洞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might give rise to its own black holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.62,0:38:08.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些黑洞 又会产生其它的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And those could lead to other universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.39,0:38:16.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许我们的宇宙就是如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe that's how our cosmos came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.97,0:38:29.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}众所周知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.81,0:38:34.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你想知道黑洞里面有什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you want to see what it's like inside a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.08,0:38:36.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要看看四周\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just look around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.99,0:38:43.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威廉・赫歇尔发现了 太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}William Herschel went on to discover that the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.66,0:38:47.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带着它的行星们 在银河系中运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its planets are moving through the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.16,0:38:49.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的儿子有什么成就呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And whatever became of his son John?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.76,0:38:52.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他成为了一位伟大的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He grew up to become a great scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.77,0:38:56.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他父亲的基础上 他所得出的外层空间观测结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His deep-space observations built on those of his father
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:59.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成为了星系标准目录的依据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to become the basis for the standard catalog of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.10,0:39:01.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沿用至今\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we use today.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.04,0:39:04.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当威廉身体不好时  约翰陪着他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When William was in failing health, John stayed with him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.28,0:39:06.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在望远镜旁 度过长夜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the long nights at his telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.28,0:39:08.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}帮他观测恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to help him sweep the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.11,0:39:13.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}父亲过世后 约翰写下墓志铭\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when his father died, John wrote his epitaph...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.12,0:39:16.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他推倒天堂的围墙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"He broke through the walls of heaven."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.80,0:39:29.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约翰经常缅怀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}John often reminisced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.47,0:39:31.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与他父亲度过的那些夏日夜晚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about those summer nights with his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.54,0:39:36.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这或许就是为何 他要寻找保存过去的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe that's why he sought a way to preserve the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.71,0:39:39.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约翰 赫歇尔 是一种展现形式的时间旅行的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}John Herschel was one of the founders
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.48,0:39:41.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}创始人之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a new form of time travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.55,0:39:45.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一种保留光线和记忆的办法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a means to capture light and memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.42,0:39:47.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他为它选择了一个名字\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He actually coined a word for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.89,0:39:50.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}摄影\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}photography.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.16,0:39:56.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你这么想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.73,0:39:59.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}摄影是时间旅行的一种形式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}photography is a form of time travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.57,0:40:03.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几百年前的人注视着我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This man is staring at us from across the centuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.07,0:40:05.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线勾勒出的鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a ghost preserved by light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:08.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不难想象 在不远的未来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not hard to imagine that in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.34,0:40:10.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以保留过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'll be able to capture the past
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.11,0:40:12.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以三维立体的形式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in all three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.34,0:40:15.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以走进一段记忆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'll be able to step inside a memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.42,0:40:23.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许不能回到过去的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may not be possible to travel backward in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.26,0:40:27.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但可能 有一天 可以将过去带来现在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but perhaps, one day, we can bring the past to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.79,0:40:32.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是我过去的一刻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's a moment from my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.03,0:40:33.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像约翰赫歇尔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like John Herschel,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.53,0:40:36.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我记得幼年的我\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm remembering a younger version of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.37,0:40:38.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1975年12月20号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}December 20, 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.97,0:40:41.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}纽约的一个雪天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A snowy day in Ithaca, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.47,0:40:44.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命旅程的一个拐点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A branchpoint on the road that brought me
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.78,0:40:47.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我有机会站在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to this moment with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.71,0:40:50.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那天我遇到了卡尔・萨根\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the day I met Carl Sagan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:57.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就如同天空中那些星星的鬼魂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Reminds me of those ghost stars in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.06,0:41:05.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使已经消亡 但星光依然照耀我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you know, the ones that still shine their light upon us long after they're gone.